{
  "stem": "13690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The most interesting part is why they had to bomb this town, which was no industry.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But five kilometers, meaning two and a half miles, was the heaviest industry of the country of Poland-- was not touched.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Meaning, in other words, they knew that this belongs to them, just to create the havoc of people [? of ?] the scariness of war.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They bombed the surrounding areas, not the industrial areas.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "On Sunday, the second day, so to say, of the war-- the first, second Sunday-- they just simply went through, like-- like, just driving through the town.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Germans came in, and they occupied the town, of course, creating various scary shootings, plundering everything possible.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the beginning.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This seemingly-- as I was, at that time, being a boy of 11, not realizing what means 'SS,' and not realizing what means 'Wehrmacht,' or what means 'Germans,' to me, a motorcycle or the cars were the interesting part to go and see.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Seemingly, I could not go and see because, just at the sight, they were just killing.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So everybody was in hiding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Not the question of Jewish population or-- the population of the town, period.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then, on Monday-- this is in the history, written many books that I found after the war-- they were considering this the Bloody Monday.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The reason the Bloody Monday was that they came into town, seemingly the black uniforms-- which later on, we found out that this is the SS 'Sturmtruppen,' so to say.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They were killing-- just merciless, merciless, wherever, just-- just killing.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Jews and Gentile, but most of them Jews that I could say.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because the Jews lived in an area in that small town close, so to say, within the vicinity.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
